Defendant Vivian D Strapp-Johnson in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, Consecutive to any other time being served, with credit for 0 days.  NO Electronic Monitoring allowed.

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.  The Court has no aversion to early termination of probation if after 18 months of Probation all conditions are fulfilled.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Perform 75 hours of community service (the Court finds this condition to be satisfied);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample;

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.   The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $5,569.82 payable to Milwaukee Public Schools(MPS) to be paid by the end of the probation period.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  The Court orders all mandatory costs WAIVED due to restitution amount ordered; the Court wants repayment to MPS.  Defendant is informed she may not possess and/or own any firearms.  Defendant is informed she may not vote in any election until her civil rights have been reinstated.
Appeal rights given. 
Filed;
